te by hub membership (routingClass 'metadata'), so there is no advisor map entry per mode and no merged-identity projection — the advisor does not read this file at runtime.\",\n  \"discriminator\": {\n    \"workflowMode\": \"Public hub/mode key. Stable identity used by the hub router and this registry. Carried by every mode.\",\n    \"backendKind\": \"Which backend runs the mode: reference-base (cites the shared design reference base under references/) or playwright-extract (runs the embedded Playwright CSS-extraction pipeline).\"\n  },\n  \"advisorRoutingContract\": {\n    \"routingClass\": \"How the advisor finds the mode. For sk-design every mode is 'metadata' = resolved by hub membership; the advisor routes the single identity sk-design and the hub picks the mode, so no mode carries an advisor map entry or a merged-identity projection.\",\n    \"packetSkillName\": \"The packet's SKILL.md name. The original flat skill name is preserved as packetSkillName; the packet folder is the short mode key, so folder != packetSkillName is grandfathered here and recorded per mode via grandfatheredFolderMismatch.\",\n    \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": \"true when the packet folder (short mode key, e.g. 'interface') differs from packetSkillName (the preserved flat name, e.g. 'interface'). All five sk-design modes preserve their original flat names, so all five are grandfathered.\"\n  },\n  \"modes\": [\n    {\n      \"workflowMode\": \"interface\",\n      \"backendKind\": \"reference-base\",\n      \"packet\": \"design-interface\",\n      \"packetSkillName\": \"design-interface\",\n      \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/mode-registry.json","text":"{\n  \"skill\": \"sk-design\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Declarative mode registry: the single source of truth for the discriminator (workflowMode/backendKind) PLUS the advisorRouting projection for sk-design. The hub reads this file to resolve a mode; the advisor routes any design query to the single identity sk-design and the hub picks the mode. All five modes route by hub membership (routingClass 'metadata'), so there is no advisor map entry per mode and no merged-identity projection — the advisor does not read this file at runtime.\",\n  \"discriminator\": {\n    \"workflowMode\": \"Public hub/mode key. Stable identity used by the hub router and this registry. Carried by every mode.\",\n    \"backendKind\": \"Which backend runs the mode: reference-base (cites the shared design reference base under references/) or playwright-extract (runs the embedded Playwright CSS-extraction pipeline).\"\n  },\n  \"advisorRoutingContract\": {\n    \"routingClass\": \"How the advisor finds the mode. For sk-design every mode is 'metadata' = resolved by hub membership; the advisor routes the single identity sk-design and the hub picks the mode, so no mode carries an advisor map entry or a merged-identity projection.\",\n    \"packetSkillName\": \"The packet's SKILL.md name. The original flat skill name is preserved as packetSkillName; the packet folder is the short mode key, so folder != packetSkillName is grandfathered here and recorded per mode via grandfatheredFolderMismatch.\",\n    \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": \"true when the packet folder (short mode key, e.g. 'interface') differs from packetSkillName (the preserved flat name, e.g. 'interface'). All five sk-design modes preserve their original flat names, so all five are grandfathered.\"\n  },\n  \"modes\": [\n    {\n      \"workflowMode\": \"interface\",\n      \"backendKind\": \"reference-base\",\n      \"packet\": \"design-interface\",\n      \"packetSkillName\": \"design-interface\",\n      \"grandfatheredFolderMismatch\": false,\n      \"aliases\": [\"interface design\", \"frontend design\", \"visual design\", \"visual identity\", \"make it look good\", \"loo