main extractions produce real similarity scores that reveal where a design system is consistent vs. fragmented — the thin dimensions signal invention-prone areas.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/150-parent-nested-skill-pattern/research/iterations/iteration-011.md:\n  Line 46:                                           //   distinct from workflowMode AND packet — REQUIRED for lexical class\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/151-sk-design-md-generator/research/iterations/iteration-026.md:\n  Line 46: 14. **[P2] dual-score-split-value-fidelity-vs-prose-provenance** — Single score (validate.ts:347) conflates value fidelity with prose provenance. A doc with all real hexes but full fabricated prose scores 99/100. Split into valuesScore (mechanical) + claimsScore (prose quality). Iter-024: valuable but adds complexity — defer until prose checks are implemented.\n\n  Line 47:    - Recommendation: validate.ts — ValidationResult gains valuesScore/claimsScore alongside score. valuesScore = existing mechanical logic. claimsScore = 100 minus penalties from checkProseDiscipline warnings + future source-sentinel checks. isPass adds claimsScore ≥ 60 gate. Guard: dual score only activates once prose checks exist — no impact on current pipeline until then.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/147-deep-loop-workflows/research/iterations/iteration-008.md:\n  Line 36: Lane C is mode-worthy, not just a helper. The operator guide defines D5 hard gate first, deterministic Mode A, optional D1-inter advisor probe, live Mode B, and opt-in D4-R ablation (`references/skill_benchmark/operator_guide.md:21-27`). It defines D1/D2/D3/D4/D5 coverage and verdict bands (`operator_guide.md:64-90`). The orchestrator resolves a target skill, runs D5 first, loads playbook scenarios, dispatches, aggregates, and writes `skill-benchmark-report.{json,md}` (`scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs:7-20`, `run-skill-benchmark.cjs:177-218`). D5 is a structural hard gate (`d5-connectivity.cjs:7-17`, `d5-connectivity.cjs:64-124`). Advisor probing is deterministic and out-of-band through the Python skill advisor (`advisor-probe.cjs:7-21`, `advisor-probe.cjs:52-72`).\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/151-sk-design-md-generator/research/iterations/iteration-009.md:\n  Line 74: 8. **[P0] A-i: altTextCoverage returns 100% when zero images exist** — a11y-extract.ts:224-249: when document.querySelectorAll('img') returns an empty NodeList, total=0 and percentage returns 100 (line 246: `total > 0 ? ... : 100`). This fabricates a perfect score from absence of data — an empty page gets \"100% alt text coverage\" which is both misleading and indistinguishable from a page where every image genuinely has alt text.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/151-sk-design-md-generator/research/iterations/iteration-029.md:\n  Line 43: 13. **[P1] Section evidence grading (per-section completeness)** — Already partially exists — validate.ts graded score (0-100) with critical gating. Next step: per-section evidence-completeness comparing writer claims against backing tokens.json. Adoption cost: MEDIUM (~60 LOC new checkEvidenceCompleteness in validate.ts).\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/151-sk-design-md-generator/research/research.md:\n  Line 9: The core defect: `validate.ts` awards 99/100 scores to DESIGN.md outputs containing wholesale prose fabrication. The validator performs 6 checks — phantom-color hex-tracing, stability-gating, unknown-font detection, format-consistency, section-header counting, and content presence — but **zero checks read a prose sentence against token ground truth** (`validate.ts:318-350`). A doc scoring 99/100 can contain \"A sleek, modern design with elegant depth principles\" — none of which has corresponding fields in `tokens.json` (`iter-026:#6`).\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/decisions/deferred_decisions.md:\n  Line 211: - Force a global rename of `04--scorer-fusion` → `05--scorer-fusion` plus `06-08` shift up, breaking spec-folder cross-references in packets 058, 098, 100, plus others.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/014-routing-benchmark/design-interface/skill-benchmark-report.md:\n  Line 21: | D5 connectivity (hard gate) | 15pts | 100/100 |\n\n  Line 64: - Mode A is the deterministic CI gate; D1-inter (advisor) + D4 (ablation) need live mode.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/012-foundations-motion-audit/spec.md:\n  Line 101: | `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/references/animation_decision_framework.md` | Create | The restraint gate for when not to animate. 100+ per day means never animate, keyboard-initiated actions never animate, and tens per day means reduce. The strongest motion anti-slop lever |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:\n  Line 107: | Expected output | `# -> expected` | `npx ts-node scripts/validate.ts ... # -> PASS, score 100` |\n\n  Line 215: - Expected execution process: run `validate.ts` against a known-good v3 Style Reference + tokens.json pair; confirm PASS with values score 100, claims score >= 80, and zero phantom-hex failures. Then plant a single hex (`#ff0000`) in a copy that does not exist in tokens.json, re-run validation, and confirm a phantom-color failure. Then plant a Quick Start hex not in tokens and confirm a critical `quickstart-phantom-color` failure, and plant a `--page-max-width: 100rem` where tokens say `100%` and confirm a `quickstart-maxwidth` warning\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/manual_testing_playbook/02--validate/002-phantom-hex-detection.md:\n  Line 40: - Expected execution process: run `validate.ts` against a known-good v3 Style Reference + tokens.json pair; confirm PASS with values score 100, claims score >= 80, and zero phantom-hex failures. Then plant a single hex (`#ff0000`) in a copy that does not exist in tokens.json, re-run validation, and confirm a phantom-color failure. Then plant a Quick Start hex not in tokens and confirm a critical `quickstart-phantom-color` failure, and plant a `--page-max-width: 100rem` where tokens say `100%` and confirm a `quickstart-maxwidth` warning\n\n\n(Results truncated. Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":100,"truncated":true},"title":"Mode A|mode A|100 of 100|100/100|motion.*100|score.*100","time":{"start":1782532370902,"end":1782532370961}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b414214e37777ed016a3f4912b928819189aae443bbf44b20"}},"id":"prt_f073571c7001T3A5R8xKW2iDgw","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c93ffeovEiyqk3ArIgPy","messageID":"msg_f0735367b001G1KCl9Imxmz1VM"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532370964,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c93ffeovEiyqk3ArIgPy","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_uGIw8d1805LhIvZblkIoZNUM","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"Mode A|mode A|100 of 100|100/100|motion.*100|score.*100","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public","include":"*.json"},"output":"Found 100 matches (more matches available)\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/152-sk-design-md-generator/research/findings-registry.json:\n  Line 1371:       \"text\": \"**[P0] A10: single score conflates value fidelity with prose provenance** — validateDesignMd (line 347) computes score = 100 - failures*5 - warnings*1. A DESIGN.md with all real hexes, complete sections, and proper format — but prose full of 'A sleek, modern design system with elegant depth principles' — scores 99/100 and passes (≥80, no critical failures). The score gives no signal that the prose is unverified filler. There is no mechanical check that prose claims (color roles, typography rationale, depth philosophy) trace back to actual token data. The prose-provenance gap is the primary hallucination vector the validator misses.\",\n\n  Line 1437:       \"text\": \"Recommendation: Split into two scores in ValidationResult: { valuesScore: number, claimsScore: number, score: number }. valuesScore = existing scoring logic (hex presence, sections, format, stability gating — all mechanical). claimsScore = 100 minus penalties from: (a) checkProseDiscipline warnings (A7 above), (b) checkProseClaims — scan descriptive paragraphs for numeric assertions (hex, px, rem, ratio) and verify each against tokens; each unverified assertion is a failure (-5), (c) checkSemanticGrounding — verify color role names in prose ('primary', 'accent', 'surface') map to actual token roles, not invented labels. score = Math.round(valuesScore * 0.6 + claimsScore * 0.4). Update isPass to require both valuesScore ≥ 80 AND claimsScore ≥ 60. Add 'unverified-claim' and 'ungrounded-semantic' to failure types (not critical — they affect claimsScore only, not hard-fail).\",\n\n  Line 1917:       \"text\": \"**[P0] A-i: altTextCoverage returns 100% when zero images exist** — a11y-extract.ts:224-249: when document.querySelectorAll('img') returns an empty NodeList, total=0 and percentage returns 100 (line 246: `total > 0 ? ... : 100`). This fabricates a perfect score from absence of data — an empty page gets \\\"100% alt text coverage\\\" which is both misleading and indistinguishable from a page where every image genuinely has alt text.\",\n\n  Line 2163:       \"text\": \"Recommendation: Design a SectionCoverageReport with shape: {sections:{number,title,tokenField,tokenCount,isEmpty,inventionRisk:none|low|medium|high}[], emptySections:string[], summary:{totalSections,backedSections,emptySections,thinSections}}. Implement as a new check (checkSectionCoverage) in validate.ts — it already reads both DESIGN.md and tokens.json. Map each of the 17 DESIGN.md sections to its DesignTokens fields (§2→colorTokens+colorRelationships, §3→typographyLevels+fontInfo, §6→shadowTokens+gradients, §6.5→motionSystem, §10→breakpoints, §11→components[*].variants[*].hoverChanges, §12→iconSystem, §2.5→darkMode, etc.). Any section with an empty/null backing token set is flagged HIGH invention risk. This is a near-zero-cost mechanical hallucination detector that catches 100% of empty-section fabrication sites.\",\n\n  Line 3369:       \"text\": \"**[P0] validate.ts:57-93,318-349 — graded validator with critical-failure gating** — The validator already produces a graded score (0-100: -5 per failure, -1 per warning) AND enforces CRITICAL_FAILURE_TYPES (phantom-color, content-color, missing-section) that hard-fail regardless of score. A single fabricated hex triggers FAIL even if all other checks pass. This is already an evidence-completeness validator, not purely binary: it distinguishes between format issues (warnings: -1) and fabrication (failures: -5, gate-failing). The score degradations per-error type create a natural severity scale.\",\n\n  Line 3387:       \"text\": \"**[P2] design-boundary-detect.ts:228-311 — cross-site similarity scores per dimension** — The boundary detector computes similarity scores per dimension (font, color, spacing, radius, component, shadow) between site groups. These are inherently confidence signals: a site with a single page scores 100 on everything (no variance = low evidence of system-ness). Multi-domain extractions produce real similarity scores that reveal where a design system is consistent vs. fragmented — the thin dimensions signal invention-prone areas.\",\n\n  Line 3549:       \"text\": \"**[P2] dual-score-split-value-fidelity-vs-prose-provenance** — Single score (validate.ts:347) conflates value fidelity with prose provenance. A doc with all real hexes but full fabricated prose scores 99/100. Split into valuesScore (mechanical) + claimsScore (prose quality). Iter-024: valuable but adds complexity — defer until prose checks are implemented.\",\n\n  Line 3735:       \"text\": \"Recommendation: validate.ts — ValidationResult gains valuesScore/claimsScore alongside score. valuesScore = existing mechanical logic. claimsScore = 100 minus penalties from checkProseDiscipline warnings + future source-sentinel checks. isPass adds claimsScore ≥ 60 gate. Guard: dual score only activates once prose checks exist — no impact on current pipeline until then.\",\n\n  Line 4287:       \"text\": \"**[P1] Section evidence grading (per-section completeness)** — Already partially exists — validate.ts graded score (0-100) with critical gating. Next step: per-section evidence-completeness comparing writer claims against backing tokens.json. Adoption cost: MEDIUM (~60 LOC new checkEvidenceCompleteness in validate.ts).\",\n\n  Line 5433:       \"text\": \"**[P0] proof.ts freshness/drift score → DESIGN.md header** — proof.ts computes a coverage score (0-100%) by sampling live-site pixels against the token palette (OKLCH deltaE<12, excluding image regions). This is a drift detector: re-running proof.ts post-extraction reveals whether the source site changed since extraction. The score is currently ephemeral (proof.html/proof-data.json). Borrowable idea: embed a 'freshness stamp' in DESIGN.md header — extractionDate, lastProofDate, coverageScore, driftStatus (FRESH/STALE/UNKNOWN). Consumers (frontend agents, CI) can gate on driftStatus before trusting tokens. Where: DESIGN.md YAML frontmatter or §0 header block.\",\n\n  Line 7383:       \"text\": \"**[P1] a11y-extract: altTextCoverage returns 100% when no images exist** — default-fabrication — Line 246: when total === 0, percentage defaults to 100. A site with zero images gets a perfect alt-text score. The DESIGN.md a11y section would claim 100% coverage without any images to assess.\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/assets/skill_benchmark/fixtures/deep-improvement/agent-improve-001.private.json:\n  Line 14:   \"notes\": \"expected.intentKeys/resources intentionally left empty until the deep-improvement SKILL.md router map is confirmed; Mode A scores structure/efficiency and treats unknown gold as non-penalizing. Populate after a router-extract pass.\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/assets/skill_benchmark/default_profile.json:\n  Line 12:   \"notes\": \"Reference profile only — NOT yet consumed at runtime. The scorer hardcodes WEIGHTS in scripts/skill-benchmark/score-skill-benchmark.cjs and there is no --profile loader on the Lane C path yet; this weights block is the forward-looking source these will read once profile loading lands. Mode A (router-replay) scores D1-intra, D2, D3, D5 deterministically; D1-inter (advisor) is built but opt-in via --advisor-mode=python; D4 (usefulness ablation) requires live mode and is reported unscored until then. Weights/bands are provisional pending 2-3 pilot calibration per the 002 playbook.\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/benchmark/after/skill-benchmark-report.json:\n  Line 26:       \"score\": 100\n\n  Line 30:       \"score\": 100\n\n  Line 89:           \"note\": \"Mode A proxy; live-mode replaces with observed-load Hit@k/Recall@k/MRR\"\n\n  Line 96:           \"note\": \"Mode A proxy; live-mode replaces with calls/tokens-to-first-expected\"\n\n  Line 124:           \"note\": \"Mode A proxy; live-mode replaces with observed-load Hit@k/Recall@k/MRR\"\n\n  Line 131:           \"note\": \"Mode A proxy; live-mode replaces with calls/tokens-to-first-expected\"\n\n  Line 150:     \"note\": \"Mode A is the deterministic CI gate; D1-inter (advisor) + D4 (ablation) need live mode.\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/benchmark/live-remediated/skill-benchmark-report.json:\n  Line 42:       \"score\": 100,\n\n  Line 85:           \"note\": \"Mode A proxy; live-mode replaces with observed-load Hit@k/Recall@k/MRR\"\n\n  Line 92:           \"note\": \"Mode A proxy; live-mode replaces with calls/tokens-to-first-expected\"\n\n  Line 153:           \"note\": \"Mode A proxy; live-mode replaces with observed-load Hit@k/Recall@k/MRR\"\n\n  Line 160:           \"note\": \"Mode A proxy; live-mode replaces with calls/tokens-to-first-expected\"\n\n  Line 219:           \"note\": \"Mode A proxy; live-mode replaces with observed-load Hit@k/Recall@k/MRR\"\n\n  Line 226:           \"note\": \"Mode A proxy; live-mode replaces with calls/tokens-to-first-expected\"\n\n  Line 318:           \"note\": \"Mode A proxy; live-mode replaces with observed-load Hit@k/Recall@k/MRR\"\n\n  Line 325:           \"note\": \"Mode A proxy; live-mode replaces with calls/tokens-to-first-expected\"\n\n  Line 377:     \"note\": \"Mode A is the deterministic CI gate; D1-inter (advisor) + D4 (ablation) need live mode.\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/benchmark/fixtures/sk-code/sk-code-loadspeed-001.private.json:\n  Line 18:   \"notes\": \"Gold intentKeys/resources are intentionally empty. Mode A replays prompt text only, but sk-code routes primarily on CWD + target file paths (surface detection FIRST, prompt keywords second). A contamination-clean prompt therefore matches no keywords and routes only to DEFAULT_RESOURCE, so positive intent/resource gold cannot be fairly scored in Mode A. Ideal routing for this task is the PERFORMANCE set (references/webflow/performance/*, references/webflow/implementation/performance_patterns.md); that gold is deferred to live Mode B, which observes real file loads given actual CWD/targets. Empty gold is non-penalizing for D1-intra/D2 per the scoring contract; the resulting D3=0 is the empty-array over-routing artifact, not a real efficiency measurement.\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/benchmark/live/skill-benchmark-report.json:\n  Line 98:           \"note\": \"Mode A proxy; live-mode replaces with observed-load Hit@k/Recall@k/MRR\"\n\n  Line 105:           \"note\": \"Mode A proxy; live-mode replaces with calls/tokens-to-first-expected\"\n\n  Line 173:           \"note\": \"Mode A proxy; live-mode replaces with observed-load Hit@k/Recall@k/MRR\"\n\n  Line 180:           \"note\": \"Mode A proxy; live-mode replaces with calls/tokens-to-first-expected\"\n\n  Line 223:           \"note\": \"Mode A proxy; live-mode replaces with observed-load Hit@k/Recall@k/MRR\"\n\n  Line 230:           \"note\": \"Mode A proxy; live-mode replaces with calls/tokens-to-first-expected\"\n\n  Line 283:     \"note\": \"Mode A is the deterministic CI gate; D1-inter (advisor) + D4 (ablation) need live mode.\"\n\n\n/Users/mic