{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1782532444067,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c93ffeovEiyqk3ArIgPy","part":{"id":"prt_f07368fa2001H6FKUEGlNn6ere","messageID":"msg_f0736886f001nibr7OVSqL8zcs","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c93ffeovEiyqk3ArIgPy","snapshot":"11dee8000c43883a585e97ac816b4c510dbb9265","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532460299,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c93ffeovEiyqk3ArIgPy","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_uE0Qtl2Zxe8ewi2Vt2vu2hB0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/manual_testing_playbook/01--strategy/001-purposeful-motion-plan.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/manual_testing_playbook/01--strategy/001-purposeful-motion-plan.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Purposeful Motion Plan Scenario\n3: description: Manual scenario verifying that motion is planned around purpose, timing, easing, and one focal choreography.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"test motion strategy\"\n6:   - \"purposeful motion scenario\"\n7:   - \"animation plan test\"\n8: importance_tier: normal\n9: contextType: reference\n10: version: 1.0.0.0\n11: expected_intent: STRATEGY\n12: expected_resources:\n13:   - references/corpus_map.md\n14:   - references/motion_strategy.md\n15: ---\n16: \n17: **Exact prompt**\n18: \n19: ```\n20: Design the motion for a product landing hero and pricing cards; make it feel premium without animating everything.\n21: ```\n22: \n23: # MOTION-STRATEGY-001 | Purposeful Motion Plan\n24: \n25: ## Prompt\n26: \n27: `Design the motion for a product landing hero and pricing cards; make it feel premium without animating everything.`\n28: \n29: ## Expected Process\n30: \n31: 1. Route to `motion`.\n32: 2. Load `references/motion_strategy.md`.\n33: 3. Pick one focal choreography and local feedback only where it clarifies state.\n34: \n35: ## Pass Criteria\n36: \n37: - Names motion purpose for each animated element.\n38: - Uses timing and easing from the reference.\n39: - Avoids scattershot scroll reveals.\n40: - Includes reduced-motion fallback.\n\n(End of file - total 40 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Purposeful Motion Plan Scenario\ndescription: Manual scenario verifying that motion is planned around purpose, timing, easing, and one focal choreography.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"test motion strategy\"\n  - \"purposeful motion scenario\"\n  - \"animation plan test\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: reference\nversion: 1.0.0.0\nexpected_intent: STRATEGY\nexpected_resources:\n  - references/corpus_map.md\n  - references/motion_strategy.md\n---\n\n**Exact prompt**\n\n```\nDesign the motion for a product landing hero and pricing cards; make it feel premium without animating everything.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/manual_testing_playbook/01--strategy/001-purposeful-motion-plan.md","text":"---\ntitle: Purposeful Motion Plan Scenario\ndescription: Manual scenario verifying that motion is planned around purpose, timing, easing, and one focal choreography.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"test motion strategy\"\n  - \"purposeful motion scenario\"\n  - \"animation plan test\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: reference\nversion: 1.0.0.0\nexpected_intent: STRATEGY\nexpected_resources:\n  - references/corpus_map.md\n  - references/motion_strategy.md\n---\n\n**Exact prompt**\n\n```\nDesign the motion for a product landing hero and pricing cards; make it feel premium without animating everything.\n```\n\n# MOTION-STRATEGY-001 | Purposeful Motion Plan\n\n## Prompt\n\n`Design the motion for a product landing hero and pricing cards; make it feel premium without animating everything.`\n\n## Expected Process\n\n1. Route to `motion`.\n2. Load `references/motion_strategy.md`.\n3. Pick one focal choreography and local feedback only where it clarifies state.\n\n## Pass Criteria\n\n- Names motion purpose for each animated element.\n- Uses timing and easing from the reference.\n- Avoids scattershot scroll reveals.\n- Includes reduced-motion fallback.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":40,"totalLines":40,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/manual_testing_playbook/01--strategy/001-purposeful-motion-plan.md","time":{"start":1782532460296,"end":1782532460299}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f67c22650c16134016a3f496c3e088191808250c0cb85084a"}},"id":"prt_f0736cf01001buKqXnbMxgHFp3","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c93ffeovEiyqk3ArIgPy","messageID":"msg_f0736886f001nibr7OVSqL8zcs"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532460367,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c93ffeovEiyqk3ArIgPy","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_F4bDuPI3ltb7BTnhucvdDA92","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/manual_testing_playbook/01--strategy/002-motion-pattern-card.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/manual_testing_playbook/01--strategy/002-motion-pattern-card.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Motion Pattern Card Scenario\n3: description: Manual scenario verifying a filled pattern card names owner, single purpose, states and reduced-motion path before handoff.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"test motion pattern card\"\n6:   - \"motion spec card scenario\"\n7:   - \"interaction card fill-in test\"\n8: importance_tier: normal\n9: contextType: reference\n10: version: 1.0.0.0\n11: expected_intent: MICRO_INTERACTIONS\n12: expected_resources:\n13:   - references/corpus_map.md\n14:   - references/micro_interactions.md\n15:   - assets/motion_pattern_cards.md\n16: ---\n17: \n18: **Exact prompt**\n19: \n20: ```\n21: Spec a toast notification and a settings drawer toggle so I can hand them to the build team.\n22: ```\n23: \n24: # MOTION-STRATEGY-002 | Motion Pattern Card\n25: \n26: ## Prompt\n27: \n28: `Spec a toast notification and a settings drawer toggle so I can hand them to the build team.`\n29: \n30: ## Expected Process\n31: \n32: 1. Run the restraint gate in `references/animation_decision_framework.md` first, then pick the matching cards in `assets/motion_pattern_cards.md` (toast card, state transition card).\n33: 2. Replace every blank cell, pulling timing and easing from `references/motion_strategy.md` rather than inventing numbers.\n34: 3. Tick the per-card checks and confirm no cell is left as a placeholder before handoff.\n35: \n36: ## Pass Criteria\n37: \n38: - Names the owner, exactly one purpose and the full state path for each card.\n39: - Cites timing and easing from `motion_strategy.md`, not new values invented in the card.\n40: - Defines a reduced-motion equivalent that keeps the state change and removes movement (toast fades only, drawer swaps instantly).\n41: - Leaves no blank cell, since a card with blanks is not ready to hand to `sk-code`.\n\n(End of file - total 41 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Motion Pattern Card Scenario\ndescription: Manual scenario verifying a filled pattern card names owner, single purpose, states and reduced-motion path before handoff.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"test motion pattern card\"\n  - \"motion spec card scenario\"\n  - \"interaction card fill-in test\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: reference\nversion: 1.0.0.0\nexpected_intent: MICRO_INTERACTIONS\nexpected_resources:\n  - references/corpus_map.md\n  - references/micro_interactions.md\n  - assets/motion_pattern_cards.md\n---\n\n**Exact prompt**\n\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/manual_testing_playbook/01--strategy/002-motion-pattern-card.md","text":"---\ntitle: Motion Pattern Card Scenario\ndescription: Manual scenario verifying a filled pattern card names owner, single purpose, states and reduced-motion path before handoff.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"test motion pattern card\"\n  - \"motion spec card scenario\"\n  - \"interaction card fill-in test\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: reference\nversion: 1.0.0.0\nexpected_intent: MICRO_INTERACTIONS\nexpected_resources:\n  - references/corpus_map.md\n  - references/micro_interactions.md\n  - assets/motion_pattern_cards.md\n---\n\n**Exact prompt**\n\n```\nSpec a toast notification and a settings drawer toggle so I can hand them to the build team.\n```\n\n# MOTION-STRATEGY-002 | Motion Pattern Card\n\n## Prompt\n\n`Spec a toast notification and a settings drawer toggle so I can hand them to the build team.`\n\n## Expected Process\n\n1. Run the restraint gate in `references/animation_decision_framework.md` first, then pick the matching cards in `assets/motion_pattern_cards.md` (toast card, state transition card).\n2. Replace every blank cell, pulling timing and easing from `references/motion_strategy.md` rather than inventing numbers.\n3. Tick the per-card checks and confirm no cell is left as a placeholder before handoff.\n\n## Pass Criteria\n\n- Names the owner, exactly one purpose and the full state path for each card.\n- Cites timing and easing from `motion_strategy.md`, not new values invented in the card.\n- Defines a reduced-motion equivalent that keeps the state change and removes movement (toast fades only, drawer swaps instantly).\n- Leaves no blank cell, since a card with blanks is not ready to hand to `sk-code`.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":41,"totalLines":41,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/manual_testing_playbook/01--strategy/002-motion-pattern-card.md","time":{"start":1782532460363,"end":1782532460366}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f67c22650c16134016a3f496c3e1c8191a7731bc1cd443852"}},"id":"prt_f0736cf3c001IKbAEmZCtYmY04","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c93ffeovEiyqk3ArIgPy","messageID":"msg_f0736886f001nibr7OVSqL8zcs"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532460409,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c93ffeovEiyqk3ArIgPy","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_XPsyZ4cUUWxweQOQgmMuSAHA","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/manual_testing_playbook/02--presence/001-animate-presence-exit-rules.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/manual_testing_playbook/02--presence/001-animate-presence-exit-rules.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: AnimatePresence Exit Rules Scenario\n3: description: Manual scenario verifying exit wrapper, exit prop, stable key, mode, and nested-exit guidance.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"test AnimatePresence\"\n6:   - \"test exit animations\"\n7:   - \"presence rules scenario\"\n8: importance_tier: normal\n9: contextType: reference\n10: version: 1.0.0.0\n11: expected_intent: PRESENCE\n12: expected_resources:\n13:   - references/corpus_map.md\n14:   - references/animate_presence_patterns.md\n15:   - assets/animate_presence_checklist.md\n16: ---\n17: \n18: **Exact prompt**\n19: \n20: ```\n21: Review this modal/list transition plan for AnimatePresence correctness before implementation.\n22: ```\n23: \n24: # MOTION-PRESENCE-001 | AnimatePresence Exit Rules\n25: \n26: ## Prompt\n27: \n28: `Review this modal/list transition plan for AnimatePresence correctness before implementation.`\n29: \n30: ## Expected Process\n31: \n32: 1. Load `references/animate_presence_patterns.md`.\n33: 2. Check wrapper, exit prop, stable key, mode, nested exits, and presence hook placement.\n34: 3. Produce concrete guidance or file:line findings when code is provided.\n35: \n36: ## Pass Criteria\n37: \n38: - Flags missing wrappers and exit props.\n39: - Rejects index keys for animated lists.\n40: - Explains `wait` duration and `popLayout` list use.\n41: - Mentions `propagate` for nested coordinated exits when relevant.\n\n(End of file - total 41 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: AnimatePresence Exit Rules Scenario\ndescription: Manual scenario verifying exit wrapper, exit prop, stable key, mode, and nested-exit guidance.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"test AnimatePresence\"\n  - \"test exit animations\"\n  - \"presence rules scenario\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: reference\nversion: 1.0.0.0\nexpected_intent: PRESENCE\nexpected_resources:\n  - references/corpus_map.md\n  - references/animate_presence_patterns.md\n  - assets/animate_presence_checklist.md\n---\n\n**Exact prompt**\n\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/manual_testing_playbook/02--presence/001-animate-presence-exit-rules.md","text":"---\ntitle: AnimatePresence Exit Rules Scenario\ndescription: Manual scenario verifying exit wrapper, exit prop, stable key, mode, and nested-exit guidance.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"test AnimatePresence\"\n  - \"test exit animations\"\n  - \"presence rules scenario\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: reference\nversion: 1.0.0.0\nexpected_intent: PRESENCE\nexpected_resources:\n  - references/corpus_map.md\n  - references/animate_presence_patterns.md\n  - assets/animate_presence_checklist.md\n---\n\n**Exact prompt**\n\n```\nReview this modal/list transition plan for AnimatePresence correctness before implementation.\n```\n\n# MOTION-PRESENCE-001 | AnimatePresence Exit Rules\n\n## Prompt\n\n`Review this modal/list transition plan for AnimatePresence correctness before implementation.`\n\n## Expected Process\n\n1. Load `references/animate_presence_patterns.md`.\n2. Check wrapper, exit prop, stable key, mode, nested exits, and presence hook placement.\n3. Produce concrete guidance or file:line findings when code is provided.\n\n## Pass Criteria\n\n- Flags missing wrappers and exit props.\n- Rejects index keys for animated lists.\n- Explains `wait` duration and `popLayout` list use.\n- Mentions `propagate` for nested coordinated exits when relevant.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":41,"totalLines":41,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/manual_testing_playbook/02--presence/001-animate-presence-exit-rules.md","time":{"start":1782532460405,"end":1782532460408}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f67c22650c16134016a3f496c3e28819194344930b6913914"}},"id":"prt_f0736cf4f001IHYlPux0pxaq6W","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c93ffeovEiyqk3ArIgPy","messageID":"msg_f0736886f001nibr7OVSqL8zcs"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532460473,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c93ffeovEiyqk3ArIgPy","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ulnymBmF7m36VRiUloBW5Mz9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/manual_testing_playbook/02--presence/002-animate-presence-checklist.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/manual_testing_playbook/02--presence/002-animate-presence-checklist.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: AnimatePresence Checklist Scenario\n3: description: Manual scenario verifying the pass-or-fail exit checklist catches wrapper, key, first-render, mode, presence-hook and nested-exit failures.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"test animate presence checklist\"\n6:   - \"exit checklist scenario\"\n7:   - \"presence pass fail test\"\n8: importance_tier: normal\n9: contextType: reference\n10: version: 1.0.0.0\n11: expected_intent: PRESENCE\n12: expected_resources:\n13:   - references/corpus_map.md\n14:   - references/animate_presence_patterns.md\n15:   - assets/animate_presence_checklist.md\n16: ---\n17: \n18: **Exact prompt**\n19: \n20: ```\n21: Here is a list component with conditional motion rows and a modal. Run the exit checklist before we ship.\n22: ```\n23: \n24: # MOTION-PRESENCE-002 | AnimatePresence Checklist\n25: \n26: ## Prompt\n27: \n28: `Here is a list component with conditional motion rows and a modal. Run the exit checklist before we ship.`\n29: \n30: ## Expected Process\n31: \n32: 1. Load `assets/animate_presence_checklist.md` and walk every section in order: exit wiring, keys, first render, mode, presence hooks, nested exits.\n33: 2. Mark each box pass or fail and record a `file:line` for any fail.\n34: 3. Point each fail to its fix in `references/animate_presence_patterns.md` rather than restating the reasoning inline.\n35: \n36: ## Pass Criteria\n37: \n38: - Flags any conditional `motion.*` element with an `exit` prop that sits outside an `AnimatePresence`.\n39: - Rejects array-index keys and confirms stable, unique data-ID keys per sibling.\n40: - Confirms `mode` matches the case and that `wait` shortens each phase, then checks `initial={false}` for default-state first mounts.\n41: - Records a `file:line` for every fail and reports it in the audit findings format from the patterns reference.\n\n(End of file - total 41 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: AnimatePresence Checklist Scenario\ndescription: Manual scenario verifying the pass-or-fail exit checklist catches wrapper, key, first-render, mode, presence-hook and nested-exit failures.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"test animate presence checklist\"\n  - \"exit checklist scenario\"\n  - \"presence pass fail test\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: reference\nversion: 1.0.0.0\nexpected_intent: PRESENCE\nexpected_resources:\n  - references/corpus_map.md\n  - references/animate_presence_patterns.md\n  - assets/animate_presence_checklist.md\n---\n\n**Exact prompt**\n\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/manual_testing_playbook/02--presence/002-animate-presence-checklist.md","text":"---\ntitle: AnimatePresence Checklist Scenario\ndescription: Manual scenario verifying the pass-or-fail exit checklist catches wrapper, key, first-render, mode, presence-hook and nested-exit failures.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"test animate presence checklist\"\n  - \"exit checklist scenario\"\n  - \"presence pass fail test\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: reference\nversion: 1.0.0.0\nexpected_intent: PRESENCE\nexpected_resources:\n  - references/corpus_map.md\n  - references/animate_presence_patterns.md\n  - assets/animate_presence_checklist.md\n---\n\n**Exact prompt**\n\n```\nHere is a list component with conditional motion rows and a modal. Run the exit checklist before we ship.\n```\n\n# MOTION-PRESENCE-002 | AnimatePresence Checklist\n\n## Prompt\n\n`Here is a list component with conditional motion rows and a modal. Run the exit checklist before we ship.`\n\n## Expected Process\n\n1. Load `assets/animate_presence_checklist.md` and walk every section in order: exit wiring, keys, first render, mode, presence hooks, nested exits.\n2. Mark each box pass or fail and record a `file:line` for any fail.\n3. Point each fail to its fix in `references/animate_presence_patterns.md` rather than restating the reasoning inline.\n\n## Pass Criteria\n\n- Flags any conditional `motion.*` element with an `exit` prop that sits outside an `AnimatePresence`.\n- Rejects array-index keys and confirms stable, unique data-ID keys per sibling.\n- Confirms `mode` matches the case and that `wait` shortens each phase, then checks `initial={false}` for default-state first mounts.\n- Records a `file:line` for every fail and reports it in the audit findings format from the patterns reference.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":41,"totalLines":41,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/manual_testing_playbook/02--presence/002-animate-presence-checklist.md","time":{"start":1782532460463,"end":1782532460471}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f67c22650c16134016a3f496c3e308191821f13d6bc0ab9af"}},"id":"prt_f0736cf7c001pjF9mlJasfRc9Q","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c93ffeovEiyqk3ArIgPy","messageID":"msg_f0736886f001nibr7OVSqL8zcs"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532460519,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c93ffeovEiyqk3ArIgPy","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Ez4iokfw9gpwjMIt2zzPNnxu","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/manual_testing_playbook/03--reduced-motion/001-performance-and-reduced-motion.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/manual_testing_playbook/03--reduced-motion/001-performance-and-reduced-motion.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Performance And Reduced Motion Scenario\n3: description: Manual scenario verifying performance-safe property choice and reduced-motion alternatives.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"test motion performance\"\n6:   - \"test reduced motion\"\n7:   - \"animation jank scenario\"\n8: importance_tier: normal\n9: contextType: reference\n10: version: 1.0.0.0\n11: expected_intent: PERFORMANCE\n12: expected_resources:\n13:   - references/corpus_map.md\n14:   - references/performance_reduced_motion.md\n15:   - assets/motion_performance_failure_card.md\n16: ---\n17: \n18: **Exact prompt**\n19: \n20: ```\n21: Plan a drawer animation with blur and layout change, but make sure it performs on mobile and respects reduced motion.\n22: ```\n23: \n24: # MOTION-REDUCED-001 | Performance And Reduced Motion\n25: \n26: ## Prompt\n27: \n28: `Plan a drawer animation with blur and layout change, but make sure it performs on mobile and respects reduced motion.`\n29: \n30: ## Expected Process\n31: \n32: 1. Load `references/performance_reduced_motion.md` and `references/motion_strategy.md`.\n33: 2. Prefer transform/opacity or FLIP for layout-like motion.\n34: 3. Bound blur/filter use and define reduced-motion behavior.\n35: \n36: ## Pass Criteria\n37: \n38: - Avoids continuous layout animation.\n39: - Names any paint-heavy effect and bounds it.\n40: - Includes reduced-motion equivalent state feedback.\n41: - Calls out mobile verification risk.\n\n(End of file - total 41 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Performance And Reduced Motion Scenario\ndescription: Manual scenario verifying performance-safe property choice and reduced-motion alternatives.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"test motion performance\"\n  - \"test reduced motion\"\n  - \"animation jank scenario\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: reference\nversion: 1.0.0.0\nexpected_intent: PERFORMANCE\nexpected_resources:\n  - references/corpus_map.md\n  - references/performance_reduced_motion.md\n  - assets/motion_performance_failure_card.md\n---\n\n**Exact prompt**\n\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/manual_testing_playbook/03--reduced-motion/001-performance-and-reduced-motion.md","text":"---\ntitle: Performance And Reduced Motion Scenario\ndescription: Manual scenario verifying performance-safe property choice and reduced-motion alternatives.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"test motion performance\"\n  - \"test reduced motion\"\n  - \"animation jank scenario\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: reference\nversion: 1.0.0.0\nexpected_intent: PERFORMANCE\nexpected_resources:\n  - references/corpus_map.md\n  - references/performance_reduced_motion.md\n  - assets/motion_performance_failure_card.md\n---\n\n**Exact prompt**\n\n```\nPlan a drawer animation with blur and layout change, but make sure it performs on mobile and respects reduced motion.\n```\n\n# MOTION-REDUCED-001 | Performance And Reduced Motion\n\n## Prompt\n\n`Plan a drawer animation with blur and layout change, but make sure it performs on mobile and respects reduced motion.`\n\n## Expected Process\n\n1. Load `references/performance_reduced_motion.md` and `references/motion_strategy.md`.\n2. Prefer transform/opacity or FLIP for layout-like motion.\n3. Bound blur/filter use and define reduced-motion behavior.\n\n## Pass Criteria\n\n- Avoids continuous layout animation.\n- Names any paint-heavy effect and bounds it.\n- Includes reduced-motion equivalent state feedback.\n- Calls out mobile verification risk.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":41,"totalLines":41,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/manual_testing_playbook/03--reduced-motion/001-performance-and-reduced-motion.md","time":{"start":1782532460514,"end":1782532460518}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f67c22650c16134016a3f496c3e34819192749c9b12f49ae8"}},"id":"prt_f0736cfd2001WMum5wfDqiVyYn","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c93ffeovEiyqk3ArIgPy","messageID":"msg_f0736886f001nibr7OVSqL8zcs"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532460527,"sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c93ffeovEiyqk3ArIgPy","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_QQvmtRQ6ablxzuYAuNAwU2w9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/manual_testing_playbook/03--reduced-motion/002-motion-performance-failure-card.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/manual_testing_playbook/03--reduced-motion/002-motion-performance-failure-card.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Motion Performance Failure Card Scenario\n3: description: Manual scenario verifying the build-side failure card catches layout thrash, scroll polling, endless rAF, mixed systems, layer promotion, paint-heavy effects and blur.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"test motion performance card\"\n6:   - \"animation jank card scenario\"\n7:   - \"dropped frames pre-handoff test\"\n8: importance_tier: normal\n9: contextType: reference\n10: version: 1.0.0.0\n11: expected_intent: PERFORMANCE\n12: expected_resources:\n13:   - references/corpus_map.md\n14:   - references/performance_reduced_motion.md\n15:   - assets/motion_performance_failure_card.md\n16: ---\n17: \n18: **Exact prompt**\n19: \n20: ```\n21: Pre-flight this scroll-driven parallax header and a drag-to-reorder list for frame drops before handoff.\n22: ```\n23: \n24: # MOTION-REDUCED-002 | Motion Performance Failure Card\n25: \n26: ## Prompt\n27: \n28: `Pre-flight this scroll-driven parallax header and a drag-to-reorder list for frame drops before handoff.`\n29: \n30: ## Expected Process\n31: \n32: 1. Load `assets/motion_performance_failure_card.md` and read each failure signature against the build.\n33: 2. Walk the rendering cost floor, keeping motion on transform and opacity unless a stated constraint forces paint or layout.\n34: 3. Apply the cheaper mechanism where a failure mode is present, then clear the pre-handoff check boxes.\n35: \n36: ## Pass Criteria\n37: \n38: - Replaces scroll-event-driven motion with a Scroll or View Timeline or `IntersectionObserver`, rather than reading `scrollY` per tick.\n39: - Catches layout thrash and any continuous `width`, `height`, `top` or `left` animation, swapping it for transform or FLIP.\n40: - Bounds blur at or below `8px` and keeps paint-heavy effects small, isolated and short-lived.\n41: - Confirms one animation system per surface, a stop condition for every `requestAnimationFrame` loop and a check on the lowest target device.\n\n(End of file - total 41 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Motion Performance Failure Card Scenario\ndescription: Manual scenario verifying the build-side failure card catches layout thrash, scroll polling, endless rAF, mixed systems, layer promotion, paint-heavy effects and blur.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"test motion performance card\"\n  - \"animation jank card scenario\"\n  - \"dropped frames pre-handoff test\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: reference\nversion: 1.0.0.0\nexpected_intent: PERFORMANCE\nexpected_resources:\n  - references/corpus_map.md\n  - references/performance_reduced_motion.md\n  - assets/motion_performance_failure_card.md\n---\n\n**Exact prompt**\n\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/manual_testing_playbook/03--reduced-motion/002-motion-performance-failure-card.md","text":"---\ntitle: Motion Performance Failure Card Scenario\ndescription: Manual scenario verifying the build-side failure card catches layout thrash, scroll polling, endless rAF, mixed systems, layer promotion, paint-heavy effects and blur.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"test motion performance card\"\n  - \"animation jank card scenario\"\n  - \"dropped frames pre-handoff test\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: reference\nversion: 1.0.0.0\nexpected_intent: PERFORMANCE\nexpected_resources:\n  - references/corpus_map.md\n  - references/performance_reduced_motion.md\n  - assets/motion_performance_failure_card.md\n---\n\n**Exact prompt**\n\n```\nPre-flight this scroll-driven parallax header and a drag-to-reorder list for frame drops before handoff.\n```\n\n# MOTION-REDUCED-002 | Motion Performance Failure Card\n\n## Prompt\n\n`Pre-flight this scroll-driven parallax header and a drag-to-reorder list for frame drops before handoff.`\n\n## Expected Process\n\n1. Load `assets/motion_performance_failure_card.md` and read each failure signature against the build.\n2. Walk the rendering cost floor, keeping motion on transform and opacity unless a stated constraint forces paint or layout.\n3. Apply the cheaper mechanism where a failure mode is present, then clear the pre-handoff check boxes.\n\n## Pass Criteria\n\n- Replaces scroll-event-driven motion with a Scroll or View Timeline or `IntersectionObserver`, rather than reading `scrollY` per tick.\n- Catches layout thrash and any continuous `width`, `height`, `top` or `left` animation, swapping it for transform or FLIP.\n- Bounds blur at or below `8px` and keeps paint-heavy effects small, isolated and short-lived.\n- Confirms one animation system per surface, a stop condition for every `requestAnimationFrame` loop and a check on the lowest target device.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":41,"totalLines":41,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/manual_testing_playbook/03--reduced-motion/002-motion-performance-failure-card.md","time":{"start":1782532460524,"end":1782532460526}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f67c22650c16134016a3f496c3e3c8191af06d4c11c218524"}},"id":"prt_f0736cfe3001d5uysVMm9e9fa8","sessionID":"ses_0f8ce9c93ffeovEiyqk3ArIgPy","messageID":"msg_f0736886f001nibr7OVSqL8zcs"}}
